description:
This is the kind of &quot;educational&quot; movies they used to show in American schools in the 1960s. This Sid Davis Production contains such quotes as:

&quot;What Jimmy didn&amp;#039;t know was that Ralph was sick; a sickness that was not visible like smallpox, but no less dangerous and contagious; a sickness of the mind. You see, Ralph was a homosexual: a person who demands an intimate relationship with members of their own sex.&quot;

And, of course:

&quot;One never knows when a homosexual is about. He may appear normal and it may be too late when you discover he is mentally ill.&quot;

This is a ten-minute short movie made in 1961. It has since lapsed into the public domain.
